Perhaps we should not add such method. One can still do the empty().putAll() trick, but adding the method would help with the following wrong pattern that we should discourage:
Mono.deferWithContext(ctx -> {
    Context.fromReadOnly(ctx).put("I have", "no idea what I am doing");
    return Mono.just("foo");
});

