I think this recommendation makes very little sense, since the same can be done with:
.flatMap(it -> Mono.deferWithContext(ctx -> doSomething(it, ctx)));
(not to mention even more optimal transformWithContext

Since this section is "simple Context examples", I'd suggest to use more... errr... "modern" way of accessing Context :D
This example can at least be rewritten as:
.flatMap(s -> Mono.deferWithContext(ctx -> Mono.just(s + " " + ctx.get(key))));
